(2, 'Page', 'Home', 'home', '', '<p><span id="undefined">Saint-Barts, it is on 21km2 only (25 including the islets on the neighborhood) and with less than 8500 inhabitants: around twenty beaches; a particularly pleasant climate all year long ; accommodation  is mainly for vacation rentals with some really luxurious villas; hotels of small size: luxury hotels,  charming hotels, boutique hotels and resorts; approximately 70 restaurants and snack bars, many private chiefs; nautical activities and great regattas involving the most beautiful sailing ships.</span>\r\n</p>\r\n<p><span id="undefined">Gustavia, the port, is also the economic center of the island where the most famous brands of luxury and the small workshop of creator-craftsmen charm customers,  mainly American,  French and European  people, and also now for Brazilian and Russian visitors. <br />St Barts is particularly famous for its gastronomical offer. Its specificity within the Caribbean rests especially in the density of its offer: restaurants, snack bars, caterers, private chiefs,… and even if one does not find there a rewarded chief, some of them or members of their brigades made their classes in the most renowned French chiefs around the world.</span>\r\n</p>\r\n<p><span id="undefined">Beyond the usual stereotypes of a luxury tourist destination, from island of the jet set or billionaires, Saint-Barts, St. Barthelemy for the purists, is thus a gastronomical destination; French traditional and gastronomical cuisine,  fusion cooking with multiple influences, the Caribbean or Asian cooking; Family restaurants and the stylish places or snack bars where one comes as it is, the atmosphere and the environement…</span>\r\n</p>', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 1, 0, 'home', 'accueil', 'St Barts Daily news of tourism leisures and restaurants', 'With StBartsLive.com, we answer to key questions ... What will I do tomorrow, today, tonight? ... Which restaurants to choose for having lunch or dinner? What''s on the menu, w